# Domain Shared Package Standards

## Purpose

`@nodestay/domain` is a pure type/validation package, depended on by `apps/web`, `apps/api`, and `packages/api-client`. It contains no business logic — only Zod schemas and inferred types.

## Module Overview

| File | Domain |
|------|--------|
| `venue.ts` | Venue, jurisdiction, regulation profile |
| `terminal.ts` | Terminal (seat device) |
| `identity.ts` | Identity verification |
| `accessPass.ts` | Access pass |
| `reservation.ts` | Reservation |
| `session.ts` | Check-in / checkout session |
| `money.ts` | Monetary amounts, currency |
| `ledger.ts` | Ledger transaction records |
| `compute.ts` | Compute nodes, jobs (ComputeNode, ComputeJob) |
| `settlement.ts` | Settlement |
| `dispute.ts` | Dispute |
| `idempotency.ts` | Idempotency key normalization |

## Coding Conventions

- Each file exports `XxxSchema` (Zod object) and `type Xxx = z.infer<typeof XxxSchema>`
- Monetary fields use the `Minor` suffix (integer, smallest currency unit)
- Status enums use `z.enum([...])` and export a standalone Status schema
- All modules are re-exported from `index.ts`
- When adding a new domain model, add `export * from './newModule'` to `index.ts`
